Virginia doing a joint program

00:00:48.660 --> 00:00:54.000
with the Culpeper Packard Campus
and The Library of Congress,

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.800
the Law Library of Congress, and
we are located on Capitol Hill,

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:00.660
the main location of the
Library in Washington,

00:01:00.660 --> 00:01:08.600
D.C. So this afternoon we are
celebrating 50 years of Miranda,

00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:11.220
and actually the basic principle

00:01:11.220 --> 00:01:17.690
of discouraging self-incrimination
is first found in history

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:22.420
in the 13th Century cited
by Moses Maimonides,

00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:25.910
who talked about the fact that
you should not force someone

00:01:25.910 --> 00:01:29.750
to be a witness against them self.

00:01:29.750 --> 00:01:35.650
And we see that in American
law, it traveled through many,

00:01:35.650 --> 00:01:39.570
many Supreme Court and lower
Court and State Court decisions,

00:01:39.570 --> 00:01:48.290
looking at how to ensure that
national values would be guaranteed

00:01:48.290 --> 00:01:53.920
in the police interrogation
aspect of criminal investigation.

00:01:53.920 --> 00:02:02.170 position:56%
So after many judicial cases Miranda
and its older sibling, Escobedo,

00:02:02.170 --> 00:02:09.440
finally reversed an 1897 case
where someone had been charged

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:14.070
with a crime based on their
confession that we believe many,

00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:17.370
many decades later
might have been coerced.

00:02:17.370 --> 00:02:22.530
But actually over the
course of the 50 years

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:30.610
since Miranda has been decided we
have learned our constitutional

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:35.500
catechism in American
society through film

00:02:35.500 --> 00:02:40.130
and TV portrayal of
the Miranda warnings.

00:02:40.130 --> 00:02:44.160
And so it is today one of
the most well-known cases

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:45.860
by the American public.

00:02:45.860 --> 00:02:49.900
Even if they don't know it by
name I think most school children

00:02:49.900 --> 00:02:53.680
who have watched television and
film and certainly most people

00:02:53.680 --> 00:02:56.580
in this room probably
could be qualified

00:02:56.580 --> 00:02:59.550
to give some form of
the Miranda warnings.

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:01.970
And the reason I say some form is

00:03:01.970 --> 00:03:10.600 position:56%
because there also have been several
cases following the 1966 decision

00:03:10.600 --> 00:03:13.740
that have reinterpreted, redefined

00:03:13.740 --> 00:03:18.670
or in essence changed
perhaps the original debate

00:03:18.670 --> 00:03:24.070 position:56%
that Miranda was involved in, and
that being part of the court looking

00:03:24.070 --> 00:03:28.430
at not wanting to - and excuse
my pun - handcuff the police

00:03:28.430 --> 00:03:32.280
and allow someone who might
have been guilty to go free.

00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:37.040
And on the other side people who
on the court who were concerned

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:42.820
that confession in general was
not the best way to prove guilt

00:03:42.820 --> 00:03:46.150
or innocence in a criminal
proceeding.

