in these films, are often old and
Caucasian, telling another story

00:44:20.050 --> 00:44:23.350
about where the weak link
in our systems might lie.

00:44:23.350 --> 00:44:27.930
There are many iconic trial films
that are based on true stories,

00:44:27.930 --> 00:44:30.800
making this ideology of
American independent minded

00:44:30.800 --> 00:44:34.950 position:56%
and determined hero even more
authoritative, even more persuasive.

00:44:34.950 --> 00:44:38.670
And although many films are
not self-explicitly referential

00:44:38.670 --> 00:44:43.770 position:56%
in their symbolism it's not uncommon
for the legal investigation leading

00:44:43.770 --> 00:44:47.050
to the trial film's climax in
these films to be structured

00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:50.830
around a visual revelation,
uncovering a missing document,

00:44:50.830 --> 00:44:55.170
a smoking gun, the critical word,
discovering a missing identity.

00:44:55.170 --> 00:44:59.490
So film's indicia of truth,
