00:45:58.590 --> 00:46:02.430
These films play on the question
of how do we know what we know,

00:46:02.430 --> 00:46:07.840 position:56%
how do we decide we know what we do,
and the law's relationship to both.

00:46:07.840 --> 00:46:09.880
Ultimately they're about the duty

00:46:09.880 --> 00:46:13.390
and difficulty of judging
as citizens.

00:46:13.390 --> 00:46:17.510
The roots of early film are in
these docudramas, they unify sight

00:46:17.510 --> 00:46:22.440
with knowledge, which is an issue
of evidence, and ways of knowing

00:46:22.440 --> 00:46:26.350
as seeing and being seen by each
other, which is about judging

00:46:26.350 --> 00:46:30.260
and objectivity and the importance
of each individual's perspective.

00:46:30.260 --> 00:46:33.700
This I would say shows the
root of law in early film.

00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:36.670
I could tell you the same
story about television,

00:46:36.670 --> 00:46:38.780
